inn1.comm: delivers from slightly wide of the crease, lands it outside off and gets it to move in slightly before reaching the keeper
bit of a scramble for that run, he was down the track and had to check the shot, dropped it in front of silly point and the non-striker set off quickly
nicely defended off the back foot, shows the full face of the bat
short and wide outside the off stump, he chops it to the off side
a touch fuller and still a touch wide outside off and left alone
watchfully left alone to the keeper, keeps it wide of the off stump
shaky outside the off stump, Nicol fishes at it, he was caught at the crease
defended inside out to the off side, had he missed that there would have been a big shout for lbw surely
prods forward and knocks it softly towards point
gets right behind the line and defends down the pitch, much better from Nicol
138 kph, quick bouncer there, Nicol had to arch back and de Villiers had to leap to collect that

gets forward and gets an inside edge to the leg side. I believe there were four overthrows there. This is what happens when the guys at the studio jump to the ad break a bit too quickly. #triggerhappy
stays back at his crease and defends
watchfully leaves it alone to the keeper
gets forward and taps it to the off side
was that really 128 kph? Got to be kidding me, that was a sharp bouncer which really caught Nicol off guard, he was airborne and the glove was not too far from the ball, best ball of the day so far
good length outside off and left alone to the keeper
defends it down to cover point
strays down the leg side and it was too quick for Guptill to flick it away
strays on the pads again and he flicks it away behind square, Tsotsobe picks it up
nervy moment for Guptill as he defends inside out late in front of the stumps, scrambles a single to cover, du Plessis collects but cannot flick it to the stumps
another sharp bouncer and Nicol rocks back early to evade it
defended softly down the pitch, testing stuff from Steyn
gets across and chops it down to the off side
slower delivery and he defends on the front foot
short and wide outside the off stump and he slaps it hard past point, had to put more effort on the shot to get it through
pushes it on the back foot to cover

is that you Jonty? Nope, it's du Plessis! Shades of the old man there at backward point, it was short and wide outside off and Guptill had to chase it, hit it hard and du Plessis had barely enough time to react, fling himself to his left and catch it mid-air, both hands behind the ball. Coaches, you might want to keep a clipping of this
gets across and gets an outside edge down to third man
gets across and defends to the on side
139 kph, beats him with a beauty outside the off stump, gets across to defend and the seam movement squares him up
139 kph again, this time McCullum leaves it with more assurance
141 kph, bangs it in short outside the off stump and he safely leaves it alone
keeps it short again and McCullum has to sway back to evade it
he gets across and nicely punches it towards midwicket, tells Nicol to wait
slower delivery down the leg side and Nicol went across to his off stump and pulled that straight to Steyn to fine leg
angles it across the right-hander and he gets across and leaves it alone
gets right across and defends to the off side
swings back in and hits him on the pad as he goes across to work it away, de Villiers thinks of challenging the umpire's not-out call but there was an inside edge anyway
short of a length and he swivels and pulls him down to deep square leg, fine leg was square enough
leading edge and safe! The ball stopped on him and it lobbed off the bat and just dropped short of de Lange running forward, could have been a wicket off his first ball on ODI debut
short down the leg side and McCullum flicks it away well wide of de Villiers
stays back and edges it down to third man, he's not looking too comfortable against de Lange
defends this one to the off side
143 kph, bouncer down the leg side and Nicol had to duck quickly
stays back and defends down the track
McCullum goes across a bit too early to pull that and he ends up getting hit on the stomach, hurried for pace there
gets across and hops at the crease as he defends to the off side
punches it back to the bowler
exaggarated movement again across the stumps as he defends
lovely timing, too much width outside off and he gets across slightly and punches it neatly past cover
very similar to the previous shot, he errs by giving width, McCullum gets across and bashes that past the diving short cover fielder
loose shot by Nicol, full and wide outside off and he was rooted to the crease as he tried to square drive it
144 kph, heads up Rob! Really sharp bouncer which just fizzed past his helmet, he was flat on his back
defends this one to the on side
146 kph, another quick one, he defends this comfortably
knocks it down to mid-on
taps it to the off side, shortish delivery
drops it short and he swivels and pulls to deep square leg
clips it down to short square leg
gets forward and drives to the off side
comes forward and gently tucks it to fine leg
fires it a bit quicker and he works it down to midwicket
pushes a full delivery down to mid-on
143 kph and McCullum goes a long way back and punches it to mid-off
fuller delivery and McCullum pushes it through the line and nearly gets a four to the long-off rope, Steyn does well to slide and cut it off
nicely punched off the back foot to the off side
145 kph, drops it full on the pads and he clips it down to fine leg
146 kph, an exaggerated shuffle across the stumps and he clips it wide of square leg, McCullum's been very busy at the crease
sharp bouncer down the leg side and he quickly gets out of the way
pushes it down to mid-on
punches it hard off the front foot to the off side, cries of 'catch'
gets across and tucks it to the on side
tries to sweep fetching that from outside off, he misses it
floated on middle and leg and he whips it to long-on
gets across and defends, the ball rolls on the pitch
tossed up on the pads and worked down to deep square
goes back, waits for the turn and punches it to the off side
works a full delivery to the on side
gets a hint of turn there and he cuts it to the off side
thin outside edge! Botha cuts back on the pace and gives it more air outside off, has Nicol poking at it outside off and de Villiers pouches the edge
waits for the turn and punches it down the track
stays back and clips it to the on side
clips it to the region of square leg
comes forward and the ball spins in and hits his pads down the leg side and there's a loud appeal
defended to the on side
driven firmly off the front foot to short cover
fires it flatter and quicker, he clips it towards midwicket
bowls it flat and he goes back and pulls to mid-on who's a bit deep, has to hurry the single
slower through the air and clipped towards midwicket
goes back and defends softly to the on side
quicker and flatter and he clips it towards midwicket
turn again, hits his pads but down the leg side
chips down the track and checks his shot as he pats it to mid-on
gets across and pushes it towards mid-off
gets across and clips it towards midwicket
nearly clips it back to the bowler on the full, checks his shot
slower ball and shorter, he rocks back and clips it towards fine leg
goes right across his stumps and defends to the off side
goes across his stumps early again to punch it off the back foot, down to long-off
skids through and he's hurried for pace as he gets an inside edge to the on side
stays back at the crease and knocks it to the off side
fuller and gets a bit of late inswing, he taps it back to the bowler
McCullum  tries to slice that through the off side but he's hurried for pace again, ends up chopping it down the pitch
139 kph, this time he gets forward and across to defend
gets across and pulls on one leg to the leg side, had to position himself quickly to play that shot
drifts on middle and leg and defended to the on side
brings out the reverse sweep and not a bad result, Amla chases from short third man
gets well forward and defends down the track
gets across and defends to the on side
stays back at the crease and plays a short arm pull down to long-on
flatter delivery, it hits his pads and rolls to the on side
short and a trifle wide, excellent square cut that beats backward point and races away
goes the other side this time, Steyn drifts on the body and he easily clips it away past the vacant spaces at square leg
140 kph, good comeback by Steyn after thise two boundaries as he cramps him up for room outside off and nearly induces an edge
skids through and he ends up chopping it towards mid-on, hurries the run
nearly carried over the rope! Williamson using the pace and bounce to his advantage, improvises well by upper cutting over first slip, inches short of the rope
stays back at the crease and defends down the track, finally a productive over for NZ
defends with soft hands down the track
he muscled that! Peterson drifts down leg and McCullum went across his stumps early, cleared the front leg and bashed that past leg slip and down to fine leg
gets forward and defends with soft hands
defended to the on side
gets across and tucks it to short square leg
gets well forward and neatly paddles it to fine leg, de Lange chases
full delivery outside off and he drives on the up towards mid-off
the change of bowling does the trick! Soft dismissal in the end, it was pitched up, McCullum looked to be driving straight but instead he got a leading edge that lobbed to backward point
comes round the wicket and sprays it wide down the leg side, work for AB
short and wide and he steers it down to third man, they put pressure on the fielder by running the second
short of a length outside off and he safely leaves it alone
closer to the off stump and he watchfully leaves it alone
short and he gets in position early to pull, but he ended up placing it straight to long leg
down the leg side and he fails to paddle it away
clips it to the on side for a single
outside edge! Franklin was really lucky it sneaked past the gap between keeper and slip
gets forward and clips it towards midwicket
punches it towards mid-off for a quick single, Franklin barely grounded his bat there, he's lucky Gavaskar was not on commentary!
short delivery from round the wicket and he swivels and pulls to the leg side
steers it to the off side
that's a fast yorker on the off stump and well dug out
gets across his stumps and tucks it to the on side
transfers his weight nicely on the back foot to defend
tucks it down to the leg side
down the track and driven to long-on
driven to long-off
gets forward and blocks it out
comes forward and steers it towards point
quicker through the air and defended
driven towards mid-off and du Plessis does an excellent job diving at short extra cover
defends softly to the on side
stabs it down to cover
whips it to deep midwicket
gets forward and defends with soft hands
tries to paddle it away but it hits his arm and dribbles away
gets well across and taps it down to the off side
short and wide and he tries to slice it away but misses
short and wide and he ends up chopping it towards point
Parnell bangs it in short and wide again and Williamson really had to reach out to cut, down to square third man and the two batsmen nearly collide during the second run
steers it down to third man, straight to the fielder this time
gets forward and drives to mid-on
spooned in the air but just wide of du Plessis's reach at short cover
full on the pads and defended towards mid-on
clips it on the full down to deep midwicket
plonks forward and defends to the off side
floated on the pads and clipped towards square leg
punches it down towards mid-off and takes a quick single, direct hit at the striker's end
opens the face of the bat and gently dabs it down to third man
138 kph, short of a length, hurries him for pace as he pulls with one hand
comes round the wicket to the right-hander, Williamson steers it to deep point
bowls a fast yorker on the pads and he manages to squirt it out
punched towards mid-on and he wisely asks Williamson to wait
chips down the track and checks his shot
squeezes out a full delivery to beat the bowler
gets well forward and defends to the off side
very good improvisation from Franklin, goes right across his stumps and paddles it down to fine leg, well wide of the fielder in the circle

Williamson doesn't bother hanging around! Just when a partnership was building. Franklin pushes it towards short cover and risks a single to du Plessis who's had a super day in the field, he charges at the ball, dives and almost in one motion flings it to de Villiers who whips off the bails, magnificent athleticism by du Plessis
down the leg side and wide called
clipped to the on side
gets an inside edge on the pads
short and wide and he cuts him down to third man
he oversteps, de Grandhomme pats it towards cover point
Free Hit: Did the best he could with that! Friendly length delivery and he clears his front leg slightly and clubs it over wide long-on, several rows back, de Grandomme's announces his ODI arrival
punches it down to cover
stays back at the crease and taps it to mid-off
drifts on the pads and he clips him to the leg side
really wide down the leg side
driven through the line down to long-on
stays back and punches it down to sweeper cover
flatter delivery and clipped to short midwicket
stays back and clips it with the turn to long-on
opens the face of the bat and steers it to short third man
gets forward and stabs it down to long-off
flights it outside off and he drives down to deep cover
stays round the wicket and he clips him down to midwicket
comes down the track and drives firmly down to long-on
gets across and punches it straight to long-on, beats Duminy's dive
stays back and punches it towards cover point
lovely shot! Duminy tosses it up from round the wicket, de Grandhomme chips down the track and sends it rows back over wide long-on
stays back and punches it down to sweeper cover
de Grandhomme continues to eye the on side, Botha bowls it short and the batsman rocks back and clubs it over midwicket
gets forward and drives towards short cover
clips it down to midwicket
works it softly down to long-on
comes well forward and defends
fullish on middle and leg and he clips him down to long-on
fullish on the pads and he clips him straight to midwicket
gets forward and drives towards sweeper
stays back and defends softly to the on side
a touch wide and he cuts it down to Parnell at sweeper cover
lands it outside off and he safely leaves it alone
goes back at the crease and tucks it to the on side
nicely punched past the covers, it was a bit too full
gets away with a half volley on the pads as he flicks it straight to fine leg
bangs it in short of a length and Franklin dabs it down to third man
once again nicely punched through the off side, beats the gap between cover and point
bowls the bouncer but de Grandhomme ducked under it early
gets beside the line and softly steers it to the off side
punches it with soft hands down to mid-on
tries to place it through the off side but chops it towards cover
clips it towards midwicket and Duminy does well to cut it off
full outside off and driven straight to cover point
over the infield, pitched up outside off and Franklin gets forward and scoops well clear of cover
fishing outside of without moving his feet, the skidder from Steyn again
drops it with soft hands but straight to backward point
teases him with width outside off and once again he misses it, beaten for pace again
a bit shorter in length outside off, this time he doesn't offer a shot
the quicker bouncer and de Grandhomme is forced to arch backwards to evade it
the pressure of the maiden over gets to de Grandhomme as he desperately swishes at one pitched up outside off, not too far from the edge
127 kph, seemed a bit quicker than that, bouncer outside off and the batsman failed to slice that over slips
shot! Tsotsobe dropped it short but it came to de Grandhomme at a friendly pace, had time to rock back and club that over deep square leg, at the MCG that would have been taken by Amla
he tries to bash that past mid-off but he misses it completely

a direct hit thwarts a budding partnership! de Grandhomme pushes it towards mid-off and he challenges Albie who takes aim at the bowler's end, the batsman's dive wasn't good enough, the third umpire takes a look but it was quite straightforward, Albie hit the stumps from a side angle
tucks it down to square leg for a single
nicely clipped away, on the pads and he whipped it in the air over midwicket, neat timing
gets across and softly steers it to the off side
gets beside the line and knocks it down to third man
stays right behind the line and defends down the track
139 kph, drops it short but strays down the leg side, surprised that wasn't called a wide
fuller delivery and he gets forward and drives softly to mid-off
fullish in length outside off and driven down to mid-off
drifts down the leg side and it clips his pads and AB does really well to stop a certain four
drops it short and he plays a short-arm pull down to deep midwicket
drifts on the pads and he clips it straight to mid-on
another short delivery and he swivels and pulls to Amla at deep square
ends the over with a fast yorker on the leg stump, nicely squeezed out
goes back at the crease and punches it down to cover
soft dismissal for Franklin, de Lange comes round the wicket and pitches it up, Franklin tries to clear the infield but ends up spooning it to Amla at short cover who takes it easily
opens the face and steers it wide of third man for a couple

pace, pace and pace! Too  good for Ellis, de Lange bangs it in short and forces Ellis to play at it, tries to fend it off but ends up lobbing it off the top end of the bat to first slip. Amla seems to be everywhere!
gets behind the line and defends to the bowler
tossed up on middle and leg and he clips it to midwicket
tossed up on middle and leg and he clips it towards square leg
NZ will need more of those, slides it too wide down the leg side, too much to ask for AB to stop that
gets well forward and drives towards long-off
defends this one to midwicket
plonks forward and defends down the track
comes forward and defends towards midwicket
just checks his shot as he defends back to the bowler
Nathan wants to push on quickly, sees the shorter length, rocks backwards and pounds that over deep midwicket
gets across and clips it to the on side

overthrows! Mills drops the ball down with soft hands and sets off, Nathan hurries and de Lange runs forward to gather the ball and turns around and throws to the bowler's end as Mills was struggling, the back up wasn't there and it went for four overthrows
how many Amlas are there on the field? Body double or not, he has taken another catch, Nathan McCullum chips it in the air straight to short midwicket, de Lange has four on debut!
ends an eventful over by drifting on the body and he easily works it down to fine leg
gets forward and tucks it to the on side
drifts on the body and he clips it down to fine leg

LBW appeal is referred, Peterson bowls it a touch flat, Mills was forward to defend and the ball hits him low on the pads quite adjacent to the leg stump, no evidence of an inside edge, Illingworth gave him out and the third umpire agrees
plonks forward and defends
stays back and defends down the track
gets forward and drives straight to cover
de Lange fires it on the blockhole and Bates does well to dig it out
on the blockhole outside the off stump and Bates nearly edges it to the keeper
clips it towards midwicket and they don't take the single
plays the checked drive and it's in the air for a few anxious seconds but it was clear of mid-off, they take three
steers it towards cover and he decides against the single
McKay does well to dig out a fast yorker, he makes room to squirt it out to third man
big cheers as NZ bring up the 200, driven down to long-off
gets forward and defends to the bowler
works it to the leg side but can't beat short fine leg
can't get straighter than that! Gets his front foot forward and a neat swing of the arms and he hits a flat six to the sightscreen
no five-for for the debutant de Lange! Peterson bowls this one which goes through with the arm and hits him flush on the front pad adjacent to the stumps

inn2.comm: on target on the off stump straightaway, Amla defends it solidly
Dropped: Guptill at short cover, checked drive by Amla and it went low to Guptill but he didn't seem ready for it
tucks him up close to the off stump and Amla gets an inside edge onto his pads
friendly half volley on the pads and he clips it away easily wide of mid-on and midwicket
holds the length back and Amla stays back at the crease and defends
keeps it outside the off stump and he safely leaves it alone to the keeper
Bates starts off nicely outside the off stump, has Albie fishing at it outside the off stump, late seam movement
fullish on the pads and clipped straight to mid-on
keeps it on a good length outside off and he chops it to the off side
short down the leg side and Parnell pulls but fails to get the desired timing, runs to fine leg
Amla shapes to drive and for the second time in this short period he gets an inside edge onto his pads
drifts on the pads and he tucks it away easily behind square on the on side
drifts on the pads and he works it down to square leg
gets across his stumps and punches it down to cover
gets beside the line and drives inside out to the off side, didn't look in full control of the shot
drives with the full face of the bat down the pitch
he oversteps! Free hit time, Amla pushes it to the off side
Free Hit, Mills is feeling generous, friendly full toss and Amla clubs it over midwicket, send him a thank you card, Hashim
watchfully leaves it alone to the keeper
stays back at the crease and punches it towards cover
bowls it short on the off stump and he swivels and pulls to square leg
punches it towards point and takes a quick single, Guptill is flat on his stomach at short cover to let the fielder take aim at the stumps but the throw is wide
lands it outside off and he leaves it alone
keeps it on the off stump and he stays back and defends
vintage Amla! Overpitched on the off stump and Amla merely drives through the line and beats mid-off, nothing more than a defensive push
tossed up on the off stump and pushed down to mid-on
goes back and chops it down to point
comes round the wicket, he comes forward and defends to the on side and takes a single
gets an inside edge on the drive to the leg side
gets forward and pushes it down to cover
drifts towards middle and leg and he tucks him to the leg side
goes back and punches him down to cover point
stays back and punches it down to cover
on the pads and he tucks it behind square on the on side
not the most convincing shot as Amla gets an inside edge to the on side as he shapes to drive
very sloppy stuff from Bates! Drifts on the pads and Parnell tucks it to fine leg, Bates had it all covered but failed to get his hands behind it properly and the ball rolled towards the rope
gets across and leaves it alone to the keeper
goes back at the crease and tucks it down to midwicket
stays back and knocks it down towards mid-off
fires it on the blockhole and Amla squirts it out to mid-off
close call for Parnell as he gets an inside edge that dribbles past the stumps
punched towards short cover who has a shy at the stumps at the bowler's end
short but not quick enough to hurry Amla, he has time to rock back and pull it over square leg
bowls it fuller and straighter and Amla gets forward and defends
Amla gets forward, stays at the crease and lofts through the line and places it wide of mid-on, the bat face turned but the timing was good enough
defends this one towards point
opens the face of the bat and steers it wide of the keeper for a quick single
Amla risks a quick single to the right of McKay but the bowler fails to gather and throw
short and wide, Parnell likes the width and he pounds it past backward point, like a proper batsman there
lands it on a good length outside the off stump and he leaves it alone
fullish in length outside the off stump and he drives towards cover
once again the short ball doesn't come off well, the pace wasn't there to trouble Parnell as he got in good position to pull over square leg, couple of bounces and four
gets across and gets an inside edge to the leg side
on the body and easily worked away wide of midwicket for a single
Dropped Nathan McCullum this time! Amla gets forward and tries to clear extra cover but he miscues it, Nathan runs backwards and nearly pulls off what looked like a tough catch
steers it down to third man for a single
gets forward and pushes it towards cover
clips it towards midwicket for another easy single
too wide outside the off stump, he easily dabs it down to third man, Mills not creating any pressure at all
tossed up on the leg stump and clipped to the on side
driven firmly but straight to short cover
driven firmly through the line to long-off
goes back, waits for the turn and punches it to the off side
bowls it flat and drops it short, Amla punishes the length by going back and pulling down to deep square leg, Franklin dives in vain
goes back and cuts him down to point
gets across and clips it with the angle to midwicket
gets across and taps it with soft hands
once again the middle and leg line by Mills allows Parnell to easy milk it away to the on side for a single
shuffles across his stumps to chase a wide delivery, he places it straight to cover point
drops it short and Amla moves across and pulls him firmly towards deep midwicket
keeps it on the off stump and he tucks it across the line back to the bowler
pushes it down to mid-off
gets across and clips it just wide of mid-on
quicker and flatter and it clips his pads perhaps outside the line of the leg stump
drives straight to short cover
jabs it firmly down to long-off
goes back at the crease and waits for the turn and cuts to cover point
Amla toys with the bowling by going across his stumps and tucking it to the on side
bangs it in short but down the leg side but Parnell doesn't offer a shot
that's more like it from Mills, troubles Parnell with the bouncer aiming at the body and he uneasily pulls it to fine leg
tries the short one again and Amla was never in full control of the pull, managed to keep it down though
short and wide and Amla cuts but ends up chopping it to N McCullum at backward point
opens the face of the bat and gently dabs it down to third man
places it down to third man and Nicol slides to cut it off and takes a chunk of turf with him
drives on the up
shapes to drive straight but checks his shot back to the bowler
Parnell goes aerial and he just manages to chip it over mid-on's reach, wasn't very convincing
tucks it to the on side
punches it down to short cover
fullish on the pads and clipped down to midwicket
steers it to backward point and that's Amla's fifty!

through the gate! Bates can't believe it and neither can Parnell because he missed a straight one, Parnell was trying to tuck it to the on side but was far too early on the shot, the ball hits off and middle
stays at crease and he leaves it to the keeper
fuller delivery outside the off stump and he pushes that towards cover
angles it across the left-hander and he leaves it alone
gets beside the line and taps it down to cover point
Amla shuffles across early and clips it down to fine leg, he knew McKay would drift towards the leg stump
goes back at the crease and defends it to the off side
fullish in length on the off stump and he drives it down to mid-off
goes back at the crease and tucks it down to fine leg
Amla fetches a short ball from outside off and slaps it wide of mid-on
stays back at the crease and punches it towards cover
pushes it towards mid-on and he risks a single to Franklin, a direct hit would have sent him back
he gets forward and checks his shot
once again he has to check his shot, slower ball this time
he shapes to cut but ends up chopping it down hard on the surface which clears silly mid-off
good change of pace by Ellis by slipping in the quicker bouncer, Amla shapes to pull but misses
thrashes a full delivery off the front foot but straight to mid-off
lands it on a good length outside the off stump and he leaves it alone
gets beside the line and chops it to the off side
the short delivery and Albie's on his toes as he pulls to the on side
bowls it full on the pads and Amla gets across and manages to flick it down to fine leg
short and wide and Morkel ends up chopping it towards extra cover
Amla moves across his stumps and turns a length delivery off his pads towards fine leg
good length outside off, the batsman aims to cover drive but he gets an outside edge towards third man
Amla moves a long way across his stumps to a straight ball and glances it fine to the boundary, high-risk shot but well executed
Amla opens the face to steer a length ball behind point
played towards silly mid-off
fullish in length outside the off stump and he drives straight to cover point
really full and wide and Amla mistimes the drive and ends up chopping it to the off side
turns the face of the bat and works it down to midwicket
Caribbean-style pull on one leg by Morkel, short on the off stump, gets nicely behind and pulls in front of square on the on side
gets forward and defends back to the bowler
full on the off stump and thrashed down to mid-off
good length on the off stump and he clips it to midwicket
uses the gentle pace of Ellis to flick it to deep square leg
quicker delivery and he knocks it to the off side
Morkel stays at the crease and pounds and length delivery on the off stump to clear long-off, lot of intent on that shot
goes higher this time! Another length delivery and he swivels and clears deep midwicket, put down by the spectator
clips it down to square leg for a single
drops it a bit short and he chops it down to extra cover
forces it down to mid-off
rocks back and punches it down to backward point
fires it full and flat and he defends close to his pads, McCullum gets a bit excited
gets forward and defends on the front foot
opens the face of the bat and steers him down to third man
drops it a bit short and he tucks it down to the on side
loses his way completely and strays far down the leg side
good length on the off stump and he dabs it to third man
gets across and taps it to the on side
drifts on the pads and he clips him down to fine leg
raw power from Albie! Pitched up on the off stump and he clears the front leg and crashes it through the line and beats mid-off
gets forward and pushes it to the off side
close call for Amla as he nearly inside edges onto his stumps on the drive, his body got in the way
gets across and clips it to the on side
